                                                                                                                                                                   Borde slams Kirsten for IPL excuse 
 
   Mumbai: Former India captain Chandu Borde Tuesday slammed coach Gary Kirsten for trotting out the Indian Premier League (IPL) as the excuse for Indias early exit from the ongoing ICC Twenty20 World Cup.   All our boys were used to this Twenty20 because of IPL. I dont know whats the difference between IPL and this World T20. The two are the same. IPL was the ideal preparation for the World Championship, Borde said. I thought Dhoni should have come up a bit instead of Ravindra Jadeja as hes one batsman who cannot be stopped once he starts getting into the groove, Borde said.      RP had one over left and I thought Dhoni should have used him instead of Ishant Sharma as he (RP) can take the ball away from the left-handers, he said.      Fans demand 
  
 Durban: Fifa Confederations Cup organisers are flooded with calls from fans asking to use some of the programmes of the Indian Premier League (IPL) in South Africa to draw supporters to the football stadiums. The calls follow concerns expressed by Fifa president Sepp Blatter that some of the Confed Cup matches had to be played in half-full stadiums.      Sreesanth hope
    Kochi: Sreesanth Tuesday said he hoped to make it to the Indian team for the Champions Trophy to be held in South Africa.   I hope to make a comeback to team India in the forthcoming Champions Trophy, he said.       Bari post
    Islamabad: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) on Tuesday named former Test cricketer Wasim Bari as chief of the interim selection committee for the tour of Sri Lanka.  According to a PCB release on Monday: Wasim Bari has been appointed as interim chairman of the selection committee to select the Pakistan cricket team for the upcoming Sri Lanka tour only.       P Sen Trophy
